Sweat dripping gasping for air about to pass out muscle burning torture that will have you looking like a Million Dollar Baby with a mere 1.5 hours of training a week.   This is an old school boxing gym.  One-on-one training.  You will be jumping rope, doing push-ups, pounding the heavy bag, and learning how to float like a butterfly.  If you are pressed for time you will not find a better workout because you are basically in the red for the entire 30 minute workout doing intervals (or "rounds").  The trainers are excellent and the environment is non-threatening.  It will put a spring in your step and get you motivated to exercise if you are in need of some extra inspiration.  You will never get bored.  I guarantee it.  You are learning a new sport, which is so much more fun than pushing weights up and down.    Recently, the owner, Joe, started a Sunday group class called "Shock Zone".  It is aptly named.  Pure torture.  I liken it to Navy Seal training.  Now that the weather has cooled off, we meet at Mesa Community College's playing fields.  Ugh.  Torture.  I already said that.  But I keep going back.  Somehow, Joe makes it fun.

